<HEADLINE> Nepali, Tibetan Artists Present Cultural Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Artists from Nepal and China's
Tibet Autonomous Region performed a colorful cultural program here
Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The performance is coincided with the China's Tibetan Art
Exhibition which opened here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Organized jointly by the Chinese Embassy in Nepal and the Royal
Nepal Academy, the performance featured by folk songs and dances
was warmly received by the audience.
</P>
<P>
Among the most popular ones are a Chinese folk song sung by
some Nepali singers and a song and dance drama called "Shepherd
and His Girlfriend" by Tibetan artists.
</P>
<P>
The 1,000-seat auditorium of the Royal Nepal Academy was fully
packed tonight. The song and dance program added a great deal of
glory to the exhibition which has drawn a large number of
visitors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
