<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Right Opposition Allies With FN in Regional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 20 (Xinhua) -- France's rightwing opposition
Liberal Democratic Party (DL), which is a splinter party of the
Union for French Democracy (UDF), Friday allied with the far-right
National Front (FN) in electing presidents of three regional
councils.
</P>
<P>
UDF-DL deputies were elected presidents of regional councils of
Languedoc-Roussillon bordering the Mediterranean, the important
industrial region of Rhone-Alpes and the big central region of
Centre with the support of FN.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the UDF deputies, including former President Valery
Giscard d'Estaing, were elected president of regional councils in
five other regions, while the Gaullist Rally for the Republic
(RPR) won two regions.
</P>
<P>
UDF and RPR deputies also failed to show up in the voting in
the Paris region, or Ile-de-France, and two other regions,
delaying the election of presidents of regional parliaments in
these regions.
</P>
<P>
The Socialist-led leftwing coalition has won only three
regional presidencies so far, and is expected to win in the
Provence-Alpes-Cote d'Azur and at least another region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
