<HEADLINE> Romania to Prioritize Development of Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Romania's transport ministry
intends to make building and improving highways its top priority.
</P>
<P>
Improving the development of railroads and the port of
Constanta are the other two other major priorities for 1998, said
Transport Minister Anton Ionescu.
</P>
<P>
Ionescu made the remark in an interview with the daily Jurnalul
National.
</P>
<P>
Romania's first highway concession opened Thursday. This and
future concessions will provide for the construction, use and
maintenance of more than 300 kilometers of highways.
</P>
<P>
The European Bank for Reconstruction and Development will issue
a credit of 53.1 million U.S. dollars toward the updating of 96
kilometers of the Bucharest-Pitesti highway.
</P>
<P>
Other concessions are expected to be commissioned during the
years 2000-2003. Provisions for the concessions will last for 30
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
