<HEADLINE> UK Experts Blow Up Bomb Left at Northern Irish Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 20 (Xinhua) -- British bomb disposal experts
Friday carried out a controlled explosion in a holdall left at a
Londonderry bank and confirmed it contained a bomb.
</P>
<P>
Two masked men had left the bag in the bank at Shipquay Place
and had told employees it held a bomb, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police also received a 20-minute warning about the device from
a caller who said he was from the Continuity IRA, a dissident
republican group opposed to peace talks on Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Workers were evacuated from offices and shops in the city
center while the security operation was carried out.
</P>
<P>
The move was apparently trying to undermine peace efforts
involving most of the province's parties in round table talks
sponsored by Britain and the Republic of Ireland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
