<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1400 GMT March 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Key members of the Israeli cabinet, also called
the inner cabinet, met Friday morning and discussed the proposed
Israeli troop withdrawal from South Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The inner cabinet ministers were briefed by Defense Minister
Yitzhak Mordechai and Chief of Staff of the Israel Defense Forces
(IDF) Lt.-Gen. Amnon Lipkin-Shahak about the military situation in
South Lebanon and discussed various proposals concerning the IDF
withdrawal from South Lebanon, the Prime Minister's Office (PMO)
said. (Israel-Lebanon)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin returned to the
Kremlin on Friday after a week-long treatment at his Gorky-9
residence.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving for the Kremlin, Yeltsin held telephone
conversations with Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, who is
currently in Odessa.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin also phoned Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov, who
briefed the president of his visit to Belgrade. (Russia-Yeltsin)
</P>
<P>
