called for an Arab summit and urged the United States to take a
more active role in pushing the peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
PNA made this call at a cabinet meeting which was held in Gaza
Thursday night on European Union's (EU) initiative for reviving
the stalled peace process brought by British Foreign Secretary
Robin Cook during his visit here earlier this week. (Israel-PNA)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- The foreign ministers of France and 45 African
countries will meet on March 24 in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso,
Agence France-Presse quoted official French sources as saying
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will set the stage for the next Franco-African
summit in Paris November 26-28, which will focus on the theme of
"Africa and questions on security." (France-Africa-FM) 
</P>
