<HEADLINE> Four-Party Talks on Korean Peninsula to Resume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing afternoon session of
the four-party talks on the Korean Peninsula has been put off till
21:30 local time (2030 GMT) while the delegations are waiting for
instructions from their capitals, a Chinese official said here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jian, China's assistant foreign minister, told reporters
that the atmosphere since the talks started on March 16 had been
"serious, calm and friendly" although there existed disagreement
on what kind of subcommittee should be set up.
</P>
<P>
"We need flexibility from all sides" to reach an agreement,
said the chairman of the current round of the talks among China,
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, South Korea and the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Chen confirmed that the talks will end no later than 9:00
Saturday local time (0800 GMT) no matter there is any agreement.
</P>
</TEXT>
