<HEADLINE> Conference of Central and Eastern European Parliaments to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Presidents of the Parliaments
from Central and Eastern European countries will meet in
Bucharest, over March 23-24, to explore ways of further development
of ties between the European Union and the associate countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the Press Department of Romanian Deputy Chamber, Jose
Maria Gil-Robles Gil-Delgado, the President of the European Parliament
will also come to the meeting, which is the fifth of its kind.
</P>
<P>
The participants in the meeting are Presidents of Parliaments from
Bulgaria, the Czech Republic, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania,
Poland, Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia.
</P>
<P>
On the agenda of the meeting is a series of debates on further
development of ties between the European Union and the associate
countries following the decisions taken by the European Council in
Luxembourg. Another matter to be discussed is the role the Parliaments
of the 10 candidate countries has to play in the countries' admission
to the EU.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Parliaments' leaders will exchange opinions and
experiences while European Parliament officials will have the
opportunity to assess the progress made by the candidate countries and
the problems they face. 
</P>
