<HEADLINE> More Visitors Watch China's Tibetan Art Exhibition  in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Every day, an average of 3,000
local and foreign people visited the China's Tibetan Art
Exhibition which opened here on Monday, according to an official
from the Chinese Embassy in Nepal that sponsored it.
</P>
<P>
On display at the six-day exhibition are about 100 pictures and
some 500 objects relating to archaeology, animal husbandry,
agriculture, dress and personal adornment, tangka and masks in
Tibet known as "the Roof of the World." Tangka is the most common
traditional art product of Tibetan Buddhism.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition which entered its fifth day Friday is also
coincided with a songs and dance performance by the Tibetan
artists Friday evening, which drew over 1,000 people. 
