<HEADLINE> TV-watching: Romanians' Favourite Amusement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 20 (Xinhua) -- TV-watching is the favourite
amusement of the Romanians. During their days-off, almost half of
them spend more than four hours watching TV, a latest survey
conducted by the Independent Center for Social Studies and Surveys
released Friday.
</P>
<P>
As many as 40 percent of the interwees said, during their
days-off, they spend more than four hours watching TV, while 24
percent up 2-4 hours watching TV programs.
</P>
<P>
News on the Government is the favourite of the news-viewers -
35 percent, followed by the business news and the social news.
</P>
<P>
A special section of the survey on the audio-visual market in
Romania shows that 96 percent of the interviewees have a TV set.
</P>
