Applied Energy Services decided last year to invest more than 400
million US dollars to build a 300-megawatt hydro dynamic power
station at upper Nile. Some American enterprises are also
involved in the telecommunication and other sectors in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the US relationship with Uganda, Susan Rice,
Assistant Secretary of State said on Wednesday in Washington that
Uganda has been a good partner of the United States and is trying
to play a largely constructive role in regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
Museveni recently expressed his welcome to Clinton's visit and
said that he hopes the visit would bring more US investment and
soft loans to improve infrastructures in the country.
</P>
<P>
During the six-African-nation trip from March 23 to April 2,
Clinton will also visit Ghana, Rwanda, South Africa, Botswana and
Senegal.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the US-Uganda relations are booming with more
frequent American officials' visits to the East African country.
One year ago, US first lady Hillary Clinton tripped Kampala, and
then Secretary of State Madeleine Albright did last December
during her tour to eight African countries. 
