<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Watches Play of 'Thunder Storm" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
also general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), watched the modern drama "Thunder Storm"
with thousands of audience members here tonight at the Capital
Theater.
</P>
<P>
The play, written by Cao Yu in 1934, focuses on portraying
emotional conflicts among members of a Chinese feudal family in
the 1920s. It has been staged by the Beijing People's Art Theater
more than 400 times, and its performance tonight affected the
audience again.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and other leading officials went onto the stage to
congratulate the actors on their performances after the play ended.
</P>
<P>
Also watching the play were leading officials Ding Guangen, Jia
Qinglin and Zheng Qinghong. 
</P>
