<DOCNO> XIE19980321.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 20th Anniversary of Deng's Speech on Science, Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Reviewing Deng Xiaoping's speech
on science and technology two decades ago is of great significance
for Chinese people to carry out the strategies of revitalizing the
country through science and education and realizing sustainable
development, Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao said here today.
</P>
<P>
Wen's remarks came while attending a meeting commemorating the
20th anniversary of the delivering of Deng's speech at the
National Science Congress in 1978, in which Deng re-established
such ideas as "science and technology is productivity" and
"intellectuals are part of the working class." Deng's speech
helped China embrace the spring of science.
</P>
<P>
With the guidance of Deng's speech, China has been earnestly
implementing the Communist Party's policy on science and
technology and intellectuals, pushing the scientific restructuring
drive, establishing systems favorable to the development of
science and technology and professional training, and promoting
the scientific and technological revolution in the agricultural
sector, Wen said, who is also a member of the Political Bureau of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China must achieve its social and economic
development on the basis of scientific and technological progress,
and the upgrading of labor's quality, placing science and
technology development and education in key positions of economic
and social development.
</P>
<P>
He required that intellectuals and knowledge must be respected
by society as a whole, and encouraged intellectuals to play their
own initiatives, adding that leading cadres must help them solve
practical problems.
</P>
<P>
Also attending the meeting were Ding Guangen, a member of the
political bureau of CPC Central Committee; Cheng Siwei, vice
chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC); and Wang Zhaoguo, Lu Jiaxi, and Song Jian, all
vice-chairmen of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
