<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Jute Meeting Begins in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Representatives from exporting and
importing members of the International Jute Organization (IJO)
began a three-day conference in Dhaka on Saturday on the situation
in the world market where competition is becoming increasingly
fierce.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the IJO's exporting countries --
Bangladesh, India, China, Nepal and Thailand and 21 importing
members including those from the European Union are attending the
26th session of the International Jute Council (IJC).
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening of the session presided over by IJC
Chairman Li Enheng of China, Bangladeshi State Minister for Jute
A.K. Faizul Huq said that jute as a natural fiber is one of the
most eco-friendly products which can be extensively used by
mankind without the environmental anxiety.
</P>
<P>
But the jute sector now faces a difficult situation in the
world market because of competition from substitute products, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"The sociological and long-term ecological benefit of jute
usage should be weighed carefully with the mere expediency of
short-term economic gains," he warned.
</P>
<P>
Jute has been a major source of income generation and a major
foreign exchange earner for a number of countries, whose total
population exceeds a billion, he said.
</P>
<P>
The fate of millions of jute growers in the developing belt is
inextricably connected with the production of jute as it plays a
significant role in poverty alleviation, he said.
</P>
<P>
IJO Executive Director K.M. Rabbani said that to make the jute
industry more profitable to the farmers and more competitive, it
is essential to evolve improved varieties which would not only
give higher yield per acre but also produce better quality fiber.
</P>
<P>
The IJO had embarked upon a project for collection,
conservation and characterization of germ plasma of jute and
allied fibers, the executive director said.
</P>
<P>
IJC Chairman Li Enheng said the objectives of the IJO had been
realized to a great extent. "This should not be taken as a
rationale for us to be self-satisfied...much more work is left to
be done," he added.
</P>
<P>
The closing meeting of the session will consider a possible
renegotiation of a successor agreement to the current
international agreement on jute and jute products in 1998,
conference sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980321.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Stresses Importance of Legislative Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, newly elected chairman
of the Standing Committee of China's Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC), today emphasized the necessity of intensifying
legislative work, improving the quality of legislation and
striving harder to build a socialist legal setup with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Li made his remarks while addressing the first meeting of the
Ninth NPC Standing Committee convened here today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
China has made great achievements toward legislative work
through two decades' of effort, he said. A legal framework has
been established with the Constitution as the core and basis, Li
said, supplemented by socialist legal systems with Chinese
features, which has played an important role in China's reform,
opening-up drive and modernization.
</P>
<P>
In the next five years China's reform will expand further and
its modernization drive will continue, he said, which will surely
set new and greater demands for the country's legislative work.
</P>
<P>
The 15th Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) has put
forward that it is necessary to tighten legislative work and
improve the quality of legislation to form a socialist legal
system with Chinese characteristics by 2010.
</P>
<P>
To realize this goal, the Ninth NPC and its Standing Committee
is entrusted with a very heavy and arduous task toward
legislation, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Li emphasized that it is imperative to seize the time, and to
draft and improve important laws concerning the socialist market
economy to standardize, guide, advance and guarantee a healthy
development of a socialist market economy in China.
</P>
<P>
Under the prerequisite of persisting in the four cardinal
principles, it is also necessary to push political restructuring
reform, improve the socialist democratic system, draft and improve
laws that help protect and guarantee people's legitimate rights as
masters of the country, and standardize administrative activities.
</P>
<P>
Li urged the formulation of a general plan for legislation
during the five-year tenure of the NPC Standing Committee, with
detailed sub-plans for each year's legislative work.
</P>
<P>
Legislative tasks should be completed in a planned,
step-by-step manner according to demand and possibility, he said.
</P>
<P>
The study and drafting of legislative outlines till the year of
2010 is also a priority, he said. The legislative outlines will
serve as guidance for long-term legislative work.
</P>
<P>
Li emphasized the necessity of drafting laws in accordance with
China's situation and practical conditions, treating the
Constitution as the basis and adhering to the unification of a
socialist legal system, associating legislation with major
decisions of China's reform and economic development, and valuing
the broad masses' opinions.
</P>
<P>
In the process of legislation, it is imperative to go deep to
investigate and research, adopt various forms and widely listen to
the opinions of the masses, said Li, adding that it is also
necessary to fully bring experts' roles in legislative work into
full play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
