<HEADLINE> Professional Job Fair Opens in Fuzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 21 (Xinhua) -- A job fair for professional
workers, co-sponsored by the Ministry of Personnel and Fujian
Province, opened today in Fuzhou, capital of east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
"It is an important step to speed up the establishment of the
country's jobs fairs for professional personnel," said a ministry
official.
</P>
<P>
The state-level fair, titled "China Straits Job Fair," was set
up to meet the demands of Taiwan-funded or foreign-funded
enterprises and push the economic and trade cooperation as well as
personnel exchanges between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Fujian Province, which faces Taiwan across the straits, has a
lot in common with Taiwan in land, blood relationships, and
cultural and language traditions. The province also has become an
important window for economic and trade exchanges between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the province had approved the
establishment of 5,000-plus Taiwan-funded enterprises with
investment hitting 5.3 billion U.S. dollars. These enterprises
need 100,000 to 120,000 employees each year.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Personnel has been promoting the establishment
of job fair systems across the country, setting up a group of
state-level or regional-level job fairs in such cities as
Shenyang, Shanghai, Wuhan, Chengdu and Xi'an.  
</P>
</TEXT>
