<HEADLINE> Beijing Starts Work on Second Largest Square </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing started today to build
its second largest square on its busiest downtown commercial
street.
</P>
<P>
Xidan Culture Square covers 2.16 hectares, of which 70 percent
will be trees and grassland. The square will be north of Chang'an
Street and serve as a place of leisure for Beijing residents.
</P>
<P>
Included in the construction is an outdoor theater, giant
sculptures, fountains and underground entertainment facilities
such as a swimming pool and skating rink.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said that the main underground construction
project will be completed by October. The whole building will
appear by Oct. 1, 1999, the 50th anniversary of the founding of
the People's Republic of China. 
</P>
