<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen asked King Norodom Sihanouk Saturday to grant a
pardon to deposed co-premier Prince Norodom Ranariddh, the king's
son, for his wrongdoings.
</P>
<P>
In a letter sent to the king, Hun Sen requested absolution
for Prince Ranariddh from two criminal convictions this month,
including the fines.
</P>
<P>
