for the general election without encountering any barricades,"
said Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
A military court sentenced the prince to five years in prison
on March 4 on an arms smuggling charge.
</P>
<P>
Another court on Wednesday convicted Ranariddh of plotting to
overthrow the government with the help of outlawed Khmer
Rouge. The court sentenced him to 30 years in prison and ordered
the prince to pay more than 50 million U.S. dollars in damages.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia is due to hold elections on July 26. 
