<HEADLINE> Li Peng Urges Improved Supervision of Government Agencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, newly elected chairman
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC),
China's top legislature, today called for more efforts to improve
supervision over governmental institutions and their workers.
</P>
<P>
"To ensure that every piece of work of the state is carried out
in accordance with the law, the governmental institutions and
their workers at various levels should, at any time, be brought
under the supervision of its people," Li Peng said at the first
meeting of the NPC Standing Committee held today in the Great Hall
of the People.
</P>
<P>
One of the prominent problems in China's legal structure is a
lack of authority under the law, Li said, adding that the
implementation of some laws is ineffective.
</P>
<P>
In many cases, laws are not strictly carried out and violations
are not looked into, he said.
</P>
<P>
The key to establishing the authority of the law is that
government bodies at various levels, especially leading officials,
should improve their consciousness of abiding by and upholding
laws, and deal with matters strictly according to law, Li said.
</P>
<P>
To promote the country's progress in accordance with law, he
said, it is necessary to ensure the implementation of the
Constitution and laws are given priority.
</P>
<P>
Li also stressed the importance of launching campaigns to
inspect the enforcement of laws and publicizing basic information
about laws.
</P>
<P>
He called on the NPC Standing Committee to make efforts to
bring under supervision every piece of work concerning state plans
and budgets, major issues of reform and construction, and issues
of great interests to the people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
