made up of Rwanda A, Burundi and Ethiopia; Group B Sudan, Kenya
and Tanzania mainland; Group C Uganda, Zanzibar and Somalia;
Group D Eritrea, Djibout and Rwanda B.
</P>
<P>
The tournament was last held in 1996 in Khartoum where host
Sudan won the cup after defeating Uganda in the final.
</P>
<P>
Rage said that the Democratic Republic of Congo is among the
three countries that have asked to be admitted to the
Confederation of East and Central African Football Association
(CECAFA).
</P>
<P>
The other two nations are Zambia and Malawi which are seeking
readmission after quitting the body in the 1980s and 1990s
respectively.
</P>
<P>
