<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traces of Siberian Tigers Confirmed in Changbai Mountains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, March 21 (Xinhua) --A United Nations investigation
team has confirmed traces of four-to-six wild Siberian tigers and
four-to-seven leopards in the forests of Changbai Mountains on the
Sino-DPRK (Democratic People's Republic of Korea) border.
</P>
<P>
The Siberian tiger is a large meat-eater mainly inhabiting
Siberia in Russia and the northeastern part of China. Only 300
Siberian tigers are believed to exist in the wild because of
difficulties in natural propagation, reduced forests providing a
natural habitat and poaching.
</P>
<P>
The 12-member team -- including specialists from China, Russia
and the United States -- conducted a concentrated investigation
with support from the U.N. Development Program Feb. 28-March
18. The area searched in Jilin Province included the cities of
Hunchun and Dunhua, and the counties of Wangqing and Antu.
</P>
<P>
Researchers on the team used such advanced research methods as
satellite positioning, said Yang Shihe, secretary-general of Jilin
Provincial Wildlife Protection Association. Yang also participated
in the U.N. investigation.
</P>
<P>
"Though we have not seen Siberian tigers and leopards with our
own eyes, we have found traces of their activities almost every
day throughout the entire investigation, including fresh tiger
footprints on the snow-covered ground, excrement, urine stains, and
bones of other animals they have eaten," said Yang, who is also
head of Forest Protection Section of Jilin Provincial Forestry
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
During the investigation, Chinese and foreign experts have also
found many roaming wild boar as well as roe, sika and red deer --
all major food sources for tigers and leopards. In Hunchun they
spotted larger numbers of wild sika deer, which have not been seen
for many years, he said.
</P>
<P>
An earlier investigation carried out in northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province found traces of at least one wild Siberian
tiger, he said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports also said traces of Siberian tigers were found
in Jiaohe city around the Lunar New Year. Those sightings were
confirmed by provincial experts.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. began investigating Siberian tigers and leopards two
years ago. So far, they have completed their investigations in
Russia and their studies in northeast China, Yang said.
</P>
<P>
The experts plan to move to the DPRK for further investigations
to estimate the number of Siberian tigers and to take effective
measures to protect them.
</P>
<P>
Leopards and Siberian tigers, listed as one of the world's 10
animal species on the verge of extinction, are on the state's
highest level of protection in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980321.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
