<HEADLINE> Cholera Kills 158 Ugandans in West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Cholera has killed 158 Ugandans
in the west part of the country, ''The New Vision'' paper
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Francis Owori, the head of cholera task forces in western
Kasese district, told the paper that preliminary statistics
indicated that 46 deaths occurred at homes, 16 in Kilembe and
four in Kagando hospitals in the district, and three more in
camps for the displaced in the district.
</P>
<P>
The two hospitals admitted 538 and 470 patients respectively
in the last 16 days, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The deaths occurred due to their delay to go to the hospitals or
health centers for treatment, a local medical report from the
district said.
</P>
<P>
Sources in Kagando hospital said 126 people had died in
neighboring east Congo (K). The hospital admitted at least 20
patients from the country.
</P>
<P>
Kasese district is still harassed by rebels of the Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF). there are at least 500 people living in
camps to escape the raids by the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Women and children are reportedly the hardest hit by the
epidemic.
</P>
<P>
A report reached here a day earlier said the disease claimed
89 people within three weeks in Kabarole, another western
district in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
