<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
rose two HK dollars Saturday to close at 2,691 HK dollars a tael,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 291.61 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, down 0.25 U.S. dollar from the previous close at Saturday's
exchange rate of one U.S. dollar to 7.7463 HK dollars. 
