<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Grants $8.2 Million to Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Japan has granted Uganda 9
billion Shillings (some 8.2 million U.S. Dollars) for purchasing
important commodities for its economic development, the press
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed Thursday by Yonezo Otake, the charge
d'affaires of Japanese Embassy, and Ugandan Finance Minister
Mayanja Nkangi.
</P>
<P>
Otake said, the grant is "to import items that are among those
permitted by the terms of the aid scheme and urgently needed to
implement the economic recovery program."
</P>
<P>
According to Ugandan finance minister, the commodities
imported will be sold and the proceeds banked on an account in
the Bank of Uganda.
</P>
<P>
"We also need the money for the balance of payments support
program," said the minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
