<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Gdp Growth Rate in 1996/97 Is 5.6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's gross domestic
product (gdp) grew by 5.6 percent in 1996/97, Minister of
Economic Development and Cooperation Girma Biru has said.
</P>
<P>
According to ''The Ethiopian Herald'' Saturday, Minister
Girma, in an interview with the official newspaper, said during
the period 1992/93 to 1996/97, the real gdp on the average grew
by about 7.0 percent annually.
</P>
<P>
Girma said the real gdp growth rate in 1996/97 is below the
average of the period.
</P>
<P>
The basic feature of the Ethiopian economy is the dominance of
the agricultural sector in terms of employment, output and export
earnings, he said, adding that hence the performance of the
economy as a whole is greatly influenced by what happens in
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The minister referred to the impacts of El Nino on Ethiopia's
agricultural production and said the El Nino in 1997 has
contributed to excess precipitation throughout equatorial eastern
Africa including Ethiopia, Kenya and Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Climate induced droughts were major social, environmental and
economic disruptive forces in Ethiopia, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, according to the U.N. Food and Agriculture
Organization and the World Food Program, Ehtiopia's total grain
production in 1997 was about 8.8 million tons compared 11.8
million tons of 1996 and 9.7 million tons in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 grain production is 25 percent and 9 percent lower
than the 1996 and 1995 respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980321.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ninth NPC Standing Committee Holds First Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Newly elected Chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's Ninth National People's Congress
(NPC) Li Peng today called on the committee to earnestly exercise
its power granted by the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark in a speech at the first meeting of the
Ninth NPC Standing Committee here.
</P>
<P>
The committee also approved the appointment of its deputy nine
secretaries-general at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Li called on the standing committee to take as
its primary responsibility safeguarding and advancing the
country's reform, opening up and the modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The committee should regard the building of socialist democracy
and legal system as its fundamental task, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li called on the committee to help improve the national
people's congress system and step up the building of a socialist
country ruled by law, so that the NPC can better play the role as
the highest organ of state power.
</P>
<P>
Li called for improving the law making work and forming a
socialist legal system with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
He called for the improvement of the supervision function to
ensure the implementation of the Constitution and other laws.
</P>
<P>
The NPC should build closer ties with the deputies and the
people, and better represent the people's interests, Li said,
</P>
<P>
He called on the committee to conduct parliamentary exchanges
with its counterpart in other countries and promote the growth of
country-to-country friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li also emphasized that the NPC should do a better job in its
daily work.  
</P>
</TEXT>
