<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province Trade With U.S. Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province's trade with the
United States amounted to 200 million U.S. dollars last year, an
increase of 30 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
The provincial foreign trade volume with the U.S. accounted
for 11.5 percent of its total, according to a report by Shaanxi's
foreign economic relations and trade department.
</P>
<P>
The province's exports rose 25.8 percent to 110 million U.S.
dollars while its imports soared by 35.9 percent to 89 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The two sides conducted foreign trade mainly in machinery,
electronics and textile products.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. companies have signed contracts to invest more than
400 million U.S. dollars in Shaanxi's more than 250 enterprises in
electronics, medical apparatus, real estate, clothing and food.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
