<HEADLINE> China's Anhui Aims to Develop Five Pillar Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province will
give priority to developing advantageous industries and
enterprises, according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
Provincial authorities have selected five pillar industries for
priority support and have decided to form 15 large enterprise
groups, the official said. The pillar industries are machinery,
electronics, automotive, chemicals and building material.
</P>
<P>
The total output value of the five pillar industries is
expected to grow an average 21.2 percent each year to 170 billion
yuan by 2000, while the 15 large enterprise groups are expected to
account for one-third of the province's industrial output value by
then.
</P>
<P>
To ensure smooth progress toward these objectives, Anhui will
invest 40 billion yuan in the selected enterprises and
industries. Thirty large, backbone projects will be launched in
the five pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
Anhui's industrial output value totaled 115.2 billion yuan last
year, 11th largest among China's all provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions, according to official statistics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
