<HEADLINE> Williams Sisters Reach Lipton's Third Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Serena Williams and Venus
Williams scored their respective wins to enter the third round of
the Lipton Championships in Key Biscayne, Florida on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Serena eliminated Irina Spirlea 7-6 (7-4), 6-0 while her elder
sister Venus defeated Tatiana Panova 6-3, 6-3 hours later.
</P>
<P>
Since October, 16-year-old Serena has soared in the WTA Tour
rankings to 40th from 453rd. She is closing in on 17-year-old
Venus who is ranked a career-best 11th.
</P>
<P>
Serena's victory was an upset over the 10th-seeded Spirlea,
which helped the Williams sisters for three consecutive wins over
the Romanian, including a victory by Venus in the semifinals at
last year's U.S. Open.
</P>
<P>
"In the second set I got a lot more balls over the net," Serena
said, adding "I knew if I could do that, she would miss."
</P>
<P>
Should the Williams sisters meet in the semifinals, Serena has
to topple defending champion Martina Hingis in the quarterfinals.
The top-ranked Hingis advanced by beating Chanda Rubin 6-1, 6-0 in
47 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the men's play, U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter was upset
by Vince Spadea 6-3, 7-5. Rafter, seeded fourth, lost in the
first round at Lipton last year.
</P>
<P>
Sixth-seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov overcame four match points in
the second set to outlast Slava Dosedel 6-7 (5-7), 7-6 (7-5), 7-6
(7-5). 
</P>
</TEXT>
