<HEADLINE> Dar Authorities Finance Women Food Vendors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Women food vendors in the
Tanzanian capital have won financial support from the government
to do business.
</P>
<P>
The Dar es Salaam City Commission has loaned women food
vendors some 150 million Shillings (about 230,000 U.S. Dollars),
said Matha Wejja, a female member of parliament.
</P>
<P>
The MP said she has been impressed by women who have struggled
to make a living by doing petty business, the Daily Mail reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Many women, particularly those with little or no income at
all, lack the necessary capital to start business, she noted.
</P>
<P>
The MP also called on non-governmental organizations (NGOs) to
issue soft loans to low-income women so as to help them start
small scale business and be able to repay the loans.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the MP advised the women to make good use
of the loans so that they can improve their living standards and
promote economic development.
</P>
<P>
However, Wejja insisted that the vendors should strive to
repay the loans in time so that other women can also get loans
from the government. 
</P>
