<HEADLINE> Vietnam Bans Players, Coach for Game Rigging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnam Football Association
has imposed lifetime ban on two players for fixing last year's
national championship game.
</P>
<P>
Also suspended was a former coach of the Ho Chi Minh City
Customs team, according to a decision by the association on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The two players, captains of Ho Chi Minh City Customs team and
the Hanoi Police team, had received bribes from bookies in
exchange for rigging the game.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Kim Hang, the banned coach, admitted to police earlier
this year that he fixed 10 out of 22 matches his team played.
</P>
<P>
The length of Hang's suspension would depend on his cooperation
with the police and the soccer body, the association said.
