<HEADLINE> Police Swoop on Uranium Seller </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Italian police seized a bar of
weapons-grade radioactive uranium and arrested 12 suspects in a
swoop on Mafia-linked traffickers Friday, police announced in the
eastern Sicilian city of Catania.
</P>
<P>
Police said the trafficking group operated between Sicily and
the region around Rome. The bar they seized contained about 190
grams of "slightly enriched" uranium.
</P>
<P>
A police officer posing as a buyer had managed to negotiate a
price for the uranium bar, going from an initial 40 billion lire
(24.2 million U.S. dollars) to 20 billion lire (12.2 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Police converged when the bar was about to be handed over.
</P>
</TEXT>
