<HEADLINE> Becker Withdraws from Lipton Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 20 (Xinhua) -- German Boris Becker, suffering
from the flu, pulled out of the Lipton championship hours before
the start of his first round at Key Biscayne, Florida on Friday.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, five-time women's champion Steffi Graf also
withdrew due to a hamstring injury.
</P>
<P>
Becker, 30, three-time Wimbledon champion, was set to compete
for the first time on the U.S. soil in two years with his last
American match dating back to Indian Wells in March, 1996.
</P>
<P>
He had withdrawn from 10 tournaments in 1997 and even pulled
out of several events in recent weeks due to an abdomenal strain
and back problems.
</P>
<P>
As the veterans became victims of injuries, Croatian teenager
Mirjana Lucic, 16, sailed into the second round of the women's
competition by overpowering Mariana Diaz-Oliva of Argentina 6-3,
6-0 in one hour.
</P>
<P>
The 46th-ranked Lucic will play 25th-ranked Russian Anna
Kournikova, who is also 16.
</P>
<P>
Both have been singled out a likely future rivals for current
number one Martina Hingis, the tournament's defending champion who
is one year their senior. 
</P>
</TEXT>
