<HEADLINE> Brazil to Order 85 Airbus Aircraft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's TAM Airline will
order 85 planes worth four billion U.S. dollars from European
Airbus.
</P>
<P>
TAM Vice President Luiz Eduardo Falco said Friday that the
company's president, Rolim Adolfo Amaro, was in Paris to sign the
contract with the European consortium.
</P>
<P>
Falco said TAM will buy 75 A320 airliners and 10 A330 aircraft
in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
The A320 model would be put into service on national and South
American lines, while the A330 model would be used on routes to
North America and Europe.
</P>
<P>
TAM Airlines now has a fleet of 30 Fokker aircraft and by the
year 2004, it will have a total of 135 aircraft. 
</P>
