<HEADLINE> China to Launch Major Technical Renovation Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- China will launch an ambitious
program to develop 500 major technical renovation projects during
the 1996-2000 period to promote technological advancement.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, which is expected to sharpen the competitive
edge of Chinese firms through technical renovation, China will
develop 5,000 key technology-intensive products, China Township
Enterprises reported.
</P>
<P>
One-hundred sixty-six key technologies, a portion of which are
expected to be put into use shortly, will be used to promote
economic growth and aid social advancement.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to technological advancement,
according to the report, and the Central Government has repeatedly
stressed that technical renovation should be given top priority in
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji said Thursday that the most important task
for his government is to invigorate the country by giving full
play to the development of science and education. 
</P>
