<HEADLINE> Chinese Yang Takes 1,500m Speedskating Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Yang Yang crossed the
finish line first to take the women's 1,500 meters title in the
Short Track Speedskating World Championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Yang, who broke the 1,000m world record in the quarter-finals
in Nagano, surged to the title in 2:26.063.
</P>
<P>
Yang finished ahead of her compatriot Wang Chunlu (2:26.347)
and Bulargia's Evgenia Radanova (2:26.501).
</P>
<P>
Olympic 1,000m champion Chun Lee-kyung of South Korea ranked in
a disappointed sixth place behind Nagano bronze medallist Won
Hye-kyung.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Marc Gagnon who crashed in the 1,000 meters final at
last month's Nagano Olympics, clinched the men's 1,500m title in
an overall time of two minutes 16.929 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Italian Fabio Carta was second in 2:17.046 while defending
champion Kim Dong-sung of South Korea had to settle with bronze in
2:17.341.
</P>
<P>
Chinese An Yulong, Olympic 500m silver medallist, was
disqualified from the race.
</P>
<P>
The world championship will continue with the men and women's
500 meters finals on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 1,000 and 3,000 meters finals as well as both relays are
scheduled for Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
