<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Olympic runner-up Frank
Fredericks of Namibia clocked 10.08 seconds to take the men's 100
meters in the third and final Grand Prix athletics meeting of the
South African season in Cape Town on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Namibian ended American Tim Montgomery's dominance of the
short sprint after the latter won the first two meetings of the
season.
</P>
<P>
The American beat Fredericks in the second event at Roodepoort
on Monday before he won the opening meet in Pietersburg where
Fredericks was absent.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Montgomery was beaten by 0.02 seconds, with his
compatriot Brian Lewis finished third in 10.20.
</P>
<P>
"This was my best run and time of the year. I'm really
pleased," Fredericks said. "I always run well in Cape Town and
things are coming together." 
