<HEADLINE> China's Ye Zhaoying Heads to Second Crown in a Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- China's world champion Ye Zhaoying
sailed into the quarterfinals of the Swiss Open badminton
tournament in Basle on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ye, who just won the All England championship last weekend,
scored an easy victory over Sweden's Karolina Ericsson 11-4, 11-2.
</P>
<P>
Of the other three semifinal berths, two were also grabbed by
the Chinese women, with second seeded Wang Chen beating Denmark's
Mette Sorensen 11-1, 11-6 and Dai Yun sweeping past another Dane
Mette Pedersen 11-2, 11-3.
</P>
<P>
Camilla Martin of Denmark defeated Indoesia's Meiluawati 11-7,
11-8 to be only non-Chinese in the women's singles semifinals.
</P>
<P>
China's All England men's singles champion Sun Jun overcame a
slow start before surging past Indonesia's Joko Suprianto 18-15,
15-4 in the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
The other three seminfinalists were all Danes. Top seed Peter
Gade Christensen rolled over compatriot Martin Lundgaard Hansen
15-4, 15-5.
</P>
<P>
He will face Kenneth Jonassen, who booked his place with a tidy
15-9, 15-7 win over Fung Permadi from Chinese Taipei.
</P>
<P>
Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen, who was awarded a walkover in the
quarterfinal over injured Ardy Wiranata of Indonesia, will face
Sun Jun in the semifinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
