<HEADLINE> Dow Jumps to above 8,900 level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
experienced a full week of advance and culminated in a gain of
staggering 103.38 points on Friday when it closed at 8,906.43, the
first time it reached the above 8,900 level.
</P>
<P>
With today's rise, the 30 blue-chip shares soared a total of
998.18 points or 12.62 percent this year. It gained 303.91 points
or 3.5 percent this week. It took the index only one day to leap
to the current level from the above 8,800 level.
</P>
<P>
psychologically confident in sound economic fundamentals,
investors ignored either worries about inflation pressure or about
the impact of Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Among top gainers today were tobacco and energy shares, as a
local jury ruled that the tobacco industry was not liable in the
death of lung cancer of a nurse exposed to passive smoking, and
oil prices were on the rise.
</P>
<P>
Most of other market indicators finished also higher with the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock list gaining 9.42 points to 1,099.16
and the New York Stock Exchange composite index up 5.23 to 572.61.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 10.82 to 1,789.16 amid
profit-taking in technology shares following their previous gains.
</P>
<P>
A hefty 709.75 million shares were changed hands against
Thursday's 572.61 million on the NYSE where advancing issues led
decliners 4-3 with 1,687 up, 1,261 down and 556 unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
