<HEADLINE> Two U.S. Submarines Collide off Long Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Two U.S. Navy nuclear-powered
submarines collided Friday during an exercise off Long Island, but
there were no injuries, the Navy said.
</P>
<P>
The extent of the damage was not immediately clear, but Navy
spokesman Lt. Cmdr. Mark McCaffrey said the damage was minor. The
submarines reached port in Connecticut under their own power to be
inspected for damage.
</P>
<P>
The submarines are the San Juan, a fast attack submarine based
in Groton, Connecticut, and the Kentucky, a Trident missile
submarine based in Kings Bay, Georgia. 
