<HEADLINE> Libya is Not Responsible for Lockerbie Bombing, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Libyan Foreign Minister
Omar Mustafa Muntasser said here Friday that Libya is not responsible
for the tragic destruction of the Pan Am jet over Lockerbie and
the horrendous loss of innocent human beings resulting therefrom.
</P>
<P>
Muntasser made the remarks at the meeting of the Security
Council of the United Nations, which held an open debate on the
question of Libya. He was the opening speaker in a day-long debate
requested by Arabian, African and other supporters of Libya.
</P>
<P>
"Insistence on the non-suspension of the sanctions imposed on
a whole people and even on the peoples of te whole region for
six years ... comes close to a clear violation of the 1948
Genocide Treaty," the Foreign Minister was responding to the
sanctions imposed on Libya since 1992.  
