<HEADLINE> Ex-leader Calls for UNITA to Headquarter in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Former General Secretary of the
National Union for Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) Eugenio
Manuvakola called for the party to move its headquarters to
Luanda on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Manuvakola, who has been dismissed from UNITA, believed that
UNITA's moving its headquarters from Bailundo to the Capital city
will greatly promote the implementation of the Lusaka Peace
Accord and the reconciliation among the Angolans.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, the UNITA ex-leader said
at a press conference here that the decision of the Political
Committee of UNITA was unfair.
</P>
<P>
Manuvakola said that UNITA is far from being a democratic
party. It needs reform from within and such a reform can only be
realized through dialogue instead of military actions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
